The rhythm R that maximizes P indicates the maximum likelihood procedure for the observed sequence of states X. As suggested by Moody and Mark1, the logarithm of the transition matrix for not_AF was divided by that of AF and used to determine the Markov score (Si) iteratively by adding each element in the resulting matrix according to the transitions between the n observed states X.

