In our work n was kept equal to the entire length of the IPI sequence. As a final step the Markov score was processed using a previously published averaging filter1. The resulting Markov score (Si) tended to decrease below zero in presence of AF and such value was compared to a threshold to make a binary decision between presence and absence of AF. The Markov model which was designed and trained using ECG data was optimized in our study to process IPI sequences from PPG for AF detection. Such optimization focused solely on fine-tuning the probability threshold applied to the Markov score (Si) to identify episodes of AF.

